│ Therefore the true branch mask must include negative classes. However,   │
│ GenericFloatingPointPredicateUtils::fcmpImpliesClass mishandles this     │
│ pattern when RHS is +0.0 and LHS is fabs(x). In the IsPositiveRHS path   │
│ with IsFabs, it transforms class sets via inverse_fabs and then maps OGt │
│ to a ClassesGE mask that does not include negative classes, leading      │
│ ValueTracking to conclude the true branch (LHS = x) is non-negative.     │
│ This causes computeKnownFPSignBit to return false, and InstSimplify      │
│ eliminates fabs incorrectly.\n\nThus, the bug is in                      │
│ GenericFloatingPointPredicateUtils.h: the mask computation for the case  │
│ \"fcmp ogt fabs(x), +0.0\" must be special-cased to yield MaskIfTrue =   │
│ ~fcZero & ~fcNan (all non-zero, any sign), and MaskIfFalse = fcZero |    │
│ fcNan.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nEdit file                          │
