  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe incorrect transformation
removes the final fabs from \"fabs(select ...)\" yielding just the select
result. Alive2 shows this is wrong for a negative subnormal input.
InstSimplify simplified \"fabs %sel\" to \"%sel\" by concluding the sign bit
of %sel is known to be zero (non-negative). That decision hinges on
computeKnownFPSignBit, which relies on computeKnownFPClass on the select,
which in turn uses fcmpImpliesClass to interpret the select condition \"fcmp
ogt (fabs x), +0.0\" as filtering the result's class.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's
Log:\nopt with --debug-only=instsimplify shows the pass replaced the final
fabs with the select (%abs2 removed, ret %sel). This simplification occurs
via InstructionSimplify::simplifyUnaryIntrinsic(), specifically:\n  case
Intrinsic::fabs:\n    if (computeKnownFPSignBit(Op0, Q) == false)\n
return Op0;\nSo, computeKnownFPSignBit(Op0) returned false (sign bit known
zero) for Op0 = %sel.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\ncomputeKnownFPClass for a
Select tries to deduce class masks from the select condition. Our condition
is \"fcmp ogt fabs(x), +0.0\". Semantically, ordered-greater-than of fabs(x)
against +0.0 is true iff x is non-zero and not NaN. That includes negative
subnormals/normals. Therefore the true branch mask must include negative
classes. However, GenericFloatingPointPredicateUtils::fcmpImpliesClass
mishandles this pattern when RHS is +0.0 and LHS is fabs(x). In the
IsPositiveRHS path with IsFabs, it transforms class sets via inverse_fabs
and then maps OGt to a ClassesGE mask that does not include negative
classes, leading ValueTracking to conclude the true branch (LHS = x) is
non-negative. This causes computeKnownFPSignBit to return false, and
InstSimplify eliminates fabs incorrectly.\n\nThus, the bug is in
GenericFloatingPointPredicateUtils.h: the mask computation for the case
\"fcmp ogt fabs(x), +0.0\" must be special-cased to yield MaskIfTrue =
~fcZero & ~fcNan (all non-zero, any sign), and MaskIfFalse = fcZero |
fcNan.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nEdit file
llvm/include/llvm/IR/GenericFloatingPointPredicateUtils.h around the
handling of IsPositiveRHS with IsFabs (lines ~360-410). Add explicit
handling when RHS is +0.0 for ordered/unsigned comparisons:\n- For fabs(x)
ogt +0.0: return {Src, ~fcZero & ~fcNan, fcZero | fcNan}.\n- For fabs(x) oge
+0.0: true for any non-NaN, so return {Src, ~fcNan, fcNan}.\n- For fabs(x)
olt +0.0: false (no magnitude less than zero), so return {Src, fcNone,
fcAllFlags}.\n- For fabs(x) ole +0.0: true exactly for zeros (non-NaN
zeros), so return {Src, fcZero, ~fcZero | fcNan}.\n- For unordered variants,
invert appropriately.\nThis ensures the true-branch mask includes negative
classes for ogt, preventing ValueTracking from concluding
non-negativity.\n\nConcrete change (at lines 360-410): inside the \"else if
(IsPositiveRHS)\" block, after computing ClassesGE/ClassesLE and before
applying inverse_fabs, insert a special-case branch:\n  if (IsFabs &&
RHSClass == fcPosZero) {\n    switch (Pred) {\n    case
FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT:\n      return {Src, ~fcZero & ~fcNan, fcZero | fcNan};\n
case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE:\n      return {Src, ~fcNan, fcNan};\n    case
FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT:\n      return {Src, fcNone, fcAllFlags};\n    case
FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE:\n      return {Src, fcZero, ~fcZero | fcNan};\n    case
FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT:\n      // unordered greater-than: true for non-zero or
NaN\n      return {Src, (~fcZero) , fcZero};\n    case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE:\n
// unordered greater-equal: true for non-NaN or NaN (always true)\n
return {Src, fcAllFlags, fcNone};\n    case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT:\n      //
unordered less-than: true for NaN only\n      return {Src, fcNan, ~fcNan};\n
case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE:\n      // unordered less-equal: true for zero or
NaN\n      return {Src, fcZero | fcNan, ~(fcZero | fcNan)};\n    default:\n
break;\n    }\n  }\nThen proceed with existing logic for other RHS.\n\nNote:
The unordered cases above follow the semantics of unordered predicates
including NaN. If preferred, they can be derived by inverting the ordered
cases per existing code style.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nBy correcting the
class-mask deduction for \"fcmp ogt fabs(x), +0.0\", ValueTracking will no
longer incorrectly assert that the select's true branch is non-negative.
Consequently, computeKnownFPSignBit(%sel) will be indeterminate (or true for
some paths), preventing InstSimplify from removing the final fabs. This
fixes the miscompile demonstrated by the reproducer and aligns class
reasoning with the semantics of fabs and ordered comparisons with zero.",
